File: Pylons carry power from South Africa's Koeberg nuclear power plant near Cape Town August 13, 2015. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will implement Stage 4-load shedding from 2pm on Tuesday. Eskom says Koeberg Unit 1 tripped resulting in it being disconnected from the grid due to a fault on the turbine side. The utility says its teams are investigating the root causes of the fault. LOAD-SHEDDING: Schedules, info, and how it affects you Eskom further said that the loss of approximately 930MW puts further strain on the generation fleet, necessitating an increase in the state of load-shedding. South Africans are urged to use electricity sparingly. Eskom says electricity demand has risen since January.